HTA programme response to the challenges of dealing with orphan medicinal 
products: Process evaluation in selected European countries.

Nicod E(1), Annemans L(2), Bucsics A(3), Lee A(4), Upadhyaya S(5), Facey K(6).

Author information:
(1)Centre for Research on Health and Social Care Management, Bocconi University, 
Via Roentgen 1, 20126 Milan, Italy; Department of Social Policy, London School 
of Economics and Political Science, Houghton Street, WC2A 2AE, London, United 
Kingdom. Electronic address: elena.nicod@unibocconi.it.
(2)Department of Public Health, Ghent University, De Pintelaan 185, 4K3, 9000 
Gent, Belgium. Electronic address: lieven.annemans@Ugent.be.
(3)Department of Finance, University of Vienna, Oskar-Morgenstern-Platz 1 (6th 
floor), 1090 Vienna, Austria. Electronic address: anna.bucsics@univie.ac.at.
(4)Scottish Medicines Consortium, Delta House (8th floor), 50 West Nile Street, 
G1 2NP Glasgow, Scotland, United Kingdom. Electronic address: annelee@nhs.net.
(5)Centre for Health Technology Evaluation, National Institute for Health and 
